Preheat the oven to 200°C. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Zest and halve the @lemon{1}(zested and halved). Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Crumble the @feta cheese{100%g} and set aside. Drain and rinse the @chickpeas{1%400g can} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a splash of @oil{a splash} in large #frying pan{} on a medium high heat. When hot add the @sliced mushrooms{150%g} and red onion, cook until the onion is soft and the mushrooms begin to colour, ~{5-6%minutes}. Meanwhile, crush the chickpeas with the back of a #fork{} or #potato masher{} until coarsely crushed.

When the mushrooms are coloured, add the chickpeas, @shawarma spice mix{1}, @honey{15%g}, @water{50%ml} and @vegetable stock powder{1}, stir to combine and dissolve the stock powder. Cook until the mixture comes together, ~{2%minutes}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if you feel it needs it.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{} combine the @low fat natural yoghurt{150%g}, lemon zest and half of the lemon juice. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir and set aside.

Trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1}(trimmed), then half lengthways. Thinly slice widthways. In a small bowl combine the remaining lemon juice and a splash of @?olive oil{splash}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the baby gem and toss to dress. Pop the @plain taco tortillas{6} in the oven for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Divide the tacos between your plates. Top with the mushroom and chickpea shawarma, then sprinkle over the feta. Top with the baby gem and coriander. Drizzle on the yoghurt. Fold and enjoy!